text: Plateau d'Hauteville is a new commune in the Ain department of eastern France. It was founded on 1 January 2019. It is made of the former communes of Cormaranche-en-Bugey, Hauteville-Lompnes, Hostiaz and Thézillieu.Arrêté préfectoral , 12 December 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Ain
title: Plateau d'Hauteville
